Content:: George Abeyagoonasekera (born 22 January 1915) was a Ceylonese politician. He was the member of Parliament of Sri Lanka from Hanguranketha representing the United National Party.[1][2] He was defeated in the by P. B. Unantenne in the 1970 general election. He was married to Rose Dagmar Seneviratne.[3]
